# 🛠 Tech Stack

- **Framework:** Next.js 15 (App Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
- **UI Kit:** Shadcn
- **Components:** Shadcn (when needed)

---

## 🗂 Folder Structure

### Components

- All UI components live in `/components`
- Organize by **feature or domain**
  - E.g., `/components/auth/LoginForm.tsx`
- Keep components **small, focused**, and **reusable**
- Prefer composition over configuration

### Actions

- All logic lives in `/actions`
- Use **Server Actions** for backend logic
- Organize by **domain**
  - E.g., `/actions/user/updateUser.ts`
- No API routes unless integrating external services

---

## 📏 Rules

- Group related components and actions into **logical folders**
- Use **TypeScript** strictly — no `any` unless unavoidable
- Use **Tailwind** for all styling — no external CSS files
- Stick to **Shadcn** components when possible
- Avoid large files — break up if over ~100 lines
- Keep functions **pure and focused** — 1 responsibility per file

---

